X-WR-CALNAME:Weaver line disruption
BEGIN:VEVENT
DESCRIPTION:<a href="https://tfl.gov.uk/tube-dlr-overground/status/?Input=&lineIds=&dateTypeSelect=Future%20date&direction=&startDate=2026-04-13T22:45:00&endDate=2026-04-14T01:29:00">Disruption map.</a>\n\nWEAVER LINE: Monday 13\, Tuesday 14\, Wednesday 15 and Thursday 16 April\, after 2245 each evening\, no service between Hackney Downs and Chingford. Replacement bus service L3 operates between Hackney Downs and Chingford via Clapton\, St James Street\, Walthamstow Central\, Wood Street and Highams Park. Last trains are at 2233 from Liverpool Street and 2255 from Chingford. The last three northbound buses leave Liverpool Street at 0014 0044 and 0114 and will also call at Bethnal Green\, Cambridge Heath and London Fields (Mare Street)
DTEND:20260414T012900Z
DTSTART:20260413T224500Z
SUMMARY:Weaver line: Part Closure
UID:ecd16d69-8831-4d5a-b33e-5f8c3c432536@ecd1.org
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DESCRIPTION:<a href="https://tfl.gov.uk/tube-dlr-overground/status/?Input=&lineIds=&dateTypeSelect=Future%20date&direction=&startDate=2026-03-19T22:45:00&endDate=2026-03-20T01:29:00">Disruption map.</a>\n\nWEAVER LINE: Monday 16\, Tuesday 17 and Thursday 19 March\, after 2245 each evening\, no service between Hackney Downs and Enfield Town / Cheshunt. Last through trains operate at 2245 from Liverpool Street to Cheshunt\, 2253 from Enfield Town to Liverpool Street\, 2300 from Liverpool Street to Enfield Town and 2302 from Cheshunt to Liverpool Street. Use Clapton for Rectory Road and Stoke Newington\, and local London Buses services for Stamford Hill. Replacement buses operate. The limited number of southbound GREATER ANGLIA and STANSTED EXPRESS trains after midnight which usually call at Seven Sisters are diverted via Tottenham Hale instead
